  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[CLEARS THROAT] And the tribunal said-- President Lawrence said, Commander Albrecht, we don't want to hear any more of that, finally.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because Albrecht was given to flowery language, colorful language.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so that was one of the things that gave us some cues, very early, as to what kind of presentation the tribunal wanted.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now, if you're quoting something very dramatic, such as I did just then, [CLEARS THROAT] just now, if you raised your voice a bit, of course, that was all right.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But they didn't want you making a description of what you were doing, which was too colorful.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They wanted it-- this laid out factually.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[CLEARS THROAT] Yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[CLEARS THROAT] In the first place, as the youth leader from way before Hitler came to power-- he was-- he'd been made youth leader even before that, and then became the Reich Youth Leader shortly after Hitler was made chancellor, in January of 1933.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The evidence I presented was mainly statements that he had made at youth gatherings, which were published in the newspapers, [CLEARS THROAT] or pamphlets which he wrote, which I said incited the youth to follow the Nazi conspirators in building a solid Nazi regime, and hence contributed to the making of aggressive war, because-- And then, he did make a number of statements.",
      "word_count": 63
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "One was quoted by a former youth leader, and we used his affidavit, where he talked the fact that-- or about the proposition that Nazi doctrines were so important that they would be accepted, eventually, across the world.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he put this in a context which indicated that they were already doing some preparations for this.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I kind of connected him up to, our notion of the conspiracy actually extended toward world domination, eventually.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
